Hello,

since syntax and indentation was a topic just recently, some VIM-advocates
might want to try the new indent feature being available in the current
development release of VIM. This requires an indent file for OCaml,
which you can get here:

  http://www.ai.univie.ac.at/~markus/vim/indent/ocaml.vim

Please tell me if you have any corrections or suggestions concerning this
file. If nobody complains about it, I'll submit it to the VIM-maintainers
for inclusion in the next release.

